The paper focuses on unsupervised imputation of missing image data using a probabilistic model and a variational approximation based on convolutional neural networks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the relationship to deep image priors, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of sparsity-aware network building blocks also suggests a potential connection to neural engineering (cs.NE) and information theory (cs.IT).
